  "description": "Electrical telegraph systems using Morse code over iron or copper wire for long-distance communication. Hub-and-spoke networks with relay stations every 50-100 km. Components: telegraph key, sounder, Daniell cell batteries, pole-line construction. Transforms coordination from days-by-courier to minutes-by-wire. Critical for railway block signaling.",
